<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880928-0153 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News: M.D.C. Asset Investors </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MIR </CO><IN> DIV </IN><TEXT>   M.D.C. ASSET INVESTORS Inc., Denver, said it will begin paying dividends monthly instead of quarterly in October.    The real estate investment trust said it is changing its dividend-payment dates to reduce volatility in its stock at the end of the quarter, when trading revolves around the dividend. The company, which has been paying 70 cents a share each quarter, said it will pay 23 cents a share on Oct. 23 to stock of record Oct. 17. </TEXT></DOC>